      • isQuoteRequestInProgress

        public static boolean isQuoteRequestInProgress(PolicyPeriod policyPeriod)
        Does the policy period have a status indicating that there is a rate/quote in progress? This method does not refresh the policy period from the database. To do that, call reloadPolicyPeriodIfAsyncQuoteComplete(PolicyPeriod)
        Parameters:
        policyPeriod - the policy period for which you want to check the status
        Returns:
        true if there is a rate/quote request in progress

      • reloadPolicyPeriodIfAsyncQuoteComplete

        public void reloadPolicyPeriodIfAsyncQuoteComplete(PolicyPeriod policyPeriod)
        Checks for the completion of an async rate/quote on a policy period. If it has completed, it will refresh the policy period from the database. If the async rate/quote has not completed, or if it was never in progress, this method will do nothing. Call this method from the UI if there is a component on the screen which is affected by the status of the policy period and there is a possibility that an async rate/quote has completed.
        Parameters:
        policyPeriod - the policyPeriod to check

      • regressToVisitableStep

        public void regressToVisitableStep()
        Does nothing if the current step is visitable. If the step is invisible, moves back to the previous visitable step.

      • refreshAndReturnPolicyPeriod

        public PolicyPeriod refreshAndReturnPolicyPeriod()

      • refreshBundle

        public void refreshBundle()
        Reloads the data for any beans in the bundle that haven't been modified. Only the data underlying the bean is changed so any references to a refreshed bean will not be affected. A bean is refreshed if a newer version exists. If a refreshed bean was deleted that bean will be evicted from the bundle.

      • getPolicyPeriod

        public PolicyPeriod getPolicyPeriod()

      • goToStep

        public void goToStep(java.lang.String stepId)
        Changes the wizard step to the one whose ID matches "stepId". If the step is not found or the step is not visitable, then throws a UserDisplayableException.
        Parameters:
        stepId - Id of wizard step to navigate to. If null, attempts to navigate to the first step of the wizard.

      • goDirectlyToStep

        public void goDirectlyToStep(java.lang.String stepId)
        Changes the wizard step to the one whose ID matches "stepId". If the step is not found or the step is not visitable, then throws a UserDisplayableException.
        Parameters:
        stepId - Id of wizard step to navigate to. If null, attempts to navigate to the first step of the wizard.

      • goDirectlyToStepWithoutWidgetValidation

        Parameters:
        stepId - ID of the wizard step to navigate to (null for the first step of the wizard)

      • newPeriod

        public PolicyPeriod newPeriod()
        Creates a new version of the PolicyPeriod that is currently active in our JobWizard and switches the wizard to view the new version.
        Returns:
        New multiquote version of PolicyPeriod
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the JobWizard's current job does not support multi-quote, or if the job already has the maximum number of versions, as determined by calling Job.getMaxNumberOfQuotes().

      • renamePeriod

        public static void renamePeriod(PolicyPeriod policyPeriod)
        Renames a PolicyPeriod using input from a Javascript prompt as the new name. The name is stored in the PolicyPeriod.BranchName field. The existing name will not be modified if the input is blank.
        Parameters:
        policyPeriod - The PolicyPeriod to rename.

      • setPeriodToView

        public PolicyPeriod setPeriodToView(PolicyPeriod policyPeriod)
        Changes the period being viewed in our JobWizard by calling JobWizard.changePolicyPeriod(PolicyPeriod). This method is used explicitly by multi-version selector. This method has no effect if the wizard's web message context is non-empty, so any errors in the currently-viewed period must be resolved before a different period can be viewed.
        Parameters:
        policyPeriod - The PolicyPeriod that should be viewed.

      • setOOSPeriodToView

        public void setOOSPeriodToView(PolicyPeriod policyPeriod)
        Changes the period being viewed in our JobWizard by calling JobWizard.changePolicyPeriod(PolicyPeriod) and checks if the wizard step is visitable. This method is used explicitly for changing the period to view using OOS slice selector. If the wizard step is not visitable, changes the period to be viewed as the original period and throws a UserDisplayableException. This method has no effect if the wizard's web message context is non-empty, so any errors in the currently-viewed period must be resolved before a different period can be viewed.
        Parameters:
        policyPeriod - The PolicyPeriod that should be viewed if visitable

      • hasActiveWorksheet

        public static boolean hasActiveWorksheet()
        Returns:

      • isInPicker

        public static boolean isInPicker()
        Returns:
        true if currently in picker, false otherwise.

      • revalidateModel

        public boolean revalidateModel()
        Calls the internal wizard reValidateModel() method, which checks for things like missing required fields and other sorts of page-level validation. This method should really only be necessary in very specific cases, such as when attempting to programatically finish a wizard such as when binding. Otherwise, the wizard framework will call this itself as needed.
        Returns:
        true if there are not blocking errors, false if there are blocking errors that should prevent the user from advancing or the wizard from finishing
